{"name": "firestart-utils", "metadata": {"name": "firestart-utils", "version": "0.2.2", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["requests"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1735556244}, "documentation": ["# Install \n\nFor Microsoft Fabric usage add it to your environments Public Libraries\n```\nfirestart-utils\n```\n\nLocal install:\n```bash\npip install firestart-utils\n```\n\n# Examples: \n\n\n## LOGGING\nImport the logger in a notebook\n\n```python\nfrom firestart_utils.logger import get_logger\n```\n\nImport lake house logger in a notebook\n```python\nfrom firestart_utils.logger import get_lakehouse_logger\n```\n\nCreate a logger object or lake house logger object\n\n!IMPORTANT logging towards datadog is only available when log_level_threshold is met\n```python\nlogger = get_logger(\"{DATADOG_API_KEY}\", \"{CUSTOMER}\", \"{ENVIROMENT}\", \"{WORKSPACE_NAME}\", \"{LOG_LEVEL_TRESHOLD}\")\n\nlakehouse_logger = get_lakehouse_logger(\"ENV\", \"location\")\n```\n\nDefault logging\n```python\nlogger.info(\"Hello World\")\nlogger.debug(\"Hello World\")\nlogger.warning(\"Hello World\")\nlogger.error(\"Hello World\")\nlogger.critical(\"Hello World\")\n```\n\nLogging pipeline metrics DataDog\n```python\nlogger.failed()\nlogger.success()\n```\n\n## UTILS\nUtils library has functions which uses the notebook utils library of Microsoft Fabric.\n\nImport the utils in a notebook\n\n```python\nfrom firestart_utils.utils import get_lakehouse, get_dump, get_secret_from_keyvault, get_runtime\n```\n### Example:\n\nGet the lakehouse object by name for accessing the lakehouse details like uid or abfsPath\n```python\nget_lakehouse.by_name(\"lakehouse_name\")\n```\n\nGet runtime object for accessing the current workspace/notebook id or name \n```python\nget_runtime().current_workspace_id()\nget_runtime().current_workspace_name()\nget_runtime().current_notebook_name()\nget_runtime().current_notebook_id()\n```\n\nGet dump of an atrribute of a object \n```python\nget_dump.by_name(Object)\n```\n\nget secret from keyvault\n```python\nget_secret_from_keyvault(\"keyvault_name\", \"secret_name\")\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "firestart_utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "firestart_utils.logger", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "firestart_utils.logger.get_logger", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "dd_api_key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dd_customer", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "environment", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "log_level", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "firestart_utils.logger.get_lakehouse_logger", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "environment", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "location", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "firestart_utils.logger.LakeHouseLogger", "xref": {"fqname": "firestart_utils.logger.logger.LakeHouseLogger", "project": null}}, {"name": "firestart_utils.logger.Logger", "xref": {"fqname": "firestart_utils.logger.logger.Logger", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "firestart_utils.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "firestart_utils.utils.get_lakehouse", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "firestart_utils.utils.get_dump", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "firestart_utils.utils.get_secret_from_keyvault", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "keyvault_name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.st